         <abstract>
            <p>New finite difference formulae of arbitrary order are derived for the special class of second-order two-point boundary value problems y" = f(x, y(x)), a ≤ x ≤ b. Variable mesh spacing is possible, and the required accuracy is achieved under a very mild mesh condition. A natural defect correction framework is set up to compute the higher-order approximations.</p>
          </abstract>
